Impax Buys 100 MW of Wind Parks in France, Poland From Eolia

-- B y   B e n   S i l l s
-- 
2011-10-17T11:11:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-17/impax-buys-100-mw-of-wind-parks-in-france-poland-from-eolia.html
Impax Asset Management Group Plc (IPX) 
bought 100 megawatts of wind farms in France and Poland from
Madrid-based Eolia Renovables, Eolia said in an e-mailed press
release.  Impax, based in London, was advised by  Norton Rose , Gomez,
Acebo & Pombo and Ernst & Young. Eolia was advised by Garrigues
and CGR Legal.  The portfolio includes operational projects and others in
development in northern and western France and in Poland near
the border with Germany.  “This deal allows us to advance our strategy of creating
an arc of regional operations covering Troyes, Amiens and
Poitiers in France,” Impax’s managing director Peter Rossbach
said in the release.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Sills at 
 bsills@bloomberg.net  